### 1-Line Logic:

> When you use the same function name but change the data type of parameters, itâ€™s called Overloading using Data Types.
> 

---

### ğŸ” Key Point:

Java allows multiple methods with the same name as long as the **parameter data types differ**.

---

### ğŸ§ª Example Code:

```java

public class Main {

    static int square(int x) {
        return x * x;
    }

    static double square(double x) {
        return x * x;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println(square(5));     // int â†’ 25
        System.out.println(square(3.5));   // double â†’ 12.25
    }
}
```

